review_blob: Probably my favorite oatmeal stout out there.  Color is perfect, mouthfeel is right on.  This beer is rather sweet, which I like in an oatmeal stout.    When I am in a liquor store and they have this beer, I buy at least one every time!
I really like this oatmeal stout.  It is a bit on the syrupy side I suppose, but overall a nice beer.  Has a nice mouthfeel and smells like an oatmeal should.  To me the color is a bit off though.

First impression was the alcohol.  I have had bigger IPAs before but with this one you could really taste the alcohol.  Basically Id say you get alcohol and hops with this one.  I wouldnt buy another.

Very pleased.  Nice citrusy  nose.  Not as bitter as I expected, but had the sweet finish I was looking for.  Pours nicely with a massive head.  Doesnt have the grapefruit of the Dreadnaught that I really want in an IPA.  I would drink this any day, but wouldnt put it at the very top of my list.
